  "text": "By Taven and Schulten (1987) , linear relations of the optically-allowed 1B u + and the optically-forbidden 2A g -, 1B u -and 3A g -singlet states were theoretically proposed. It was also shown that the slopes of the 2A g -, 1B u -and 3A g -optically-forbidden singlet states, as functions of 1/ (2n + 1), exhibit the ratio of ~2:3:4, respectively. The slopes of the 2A g -, 1B u -and 3A g -states determined by measurement of resonance-Raman excitation profiles of crystalline Cars (n = 9-13) turned out to be 2:3.1:3.8 ( Fig. 1a ; [CITATION_1] , were in excellent agreement with those determined by a theoretical calculation, i.e., 2:3.1:3.7 [CITATION_2] .",
